{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 Import A1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To import the A1 data set into the MySQL, the binary event stream needs to be converted first. The conversion takes the binary event stream and converts its to CSV file. Each row in the CSV file represents an event. Later the created CSV file will be imported into the database similar to Listing\u160?[lst:textmysql].\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Convert\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The conversion is carried out a by a Java program which takes the binary data stream as input and outputs a CSV file. First a Java {\f1 InputStream} from the input file will be created. This input stream will be passed to a {\f1 DataInputStream}. As illustrated in Listing\u160?[lst:parsestream] a loop iterates over the data input stream and parses the binary information according to the A1 data structure. At last at the end of each iteration the parsed information will be print to the standard output.\par}
